Product or Service Description: IT AND TELECOM- TELECOMMUNICATIONS NETWORK MANAGEMENT
Description of Requirement:
NASA GODDARD SPACE FLIGHT CENTER'S (GSFC) GOAL FOR THE SPACE COMMUNICATIONS NETWORKS SERVICES CONTRACT (SCNS) IS TO ENABLE MISSION SUCCESS FOR EVERY CUSTOMER USING SCNS SERVICES.  KEY OBJECTIVES OF THE SCNS CONTRACT ARE TO DECREASE COST AND MAINTAIN OR IMPROVE OPERATIONAL EFFICIENCY AND RELIABILITY, WHILE MAINTAINING AN ACCEPTABLE LEVEL OF RISK AND PROVIDING FOR SAFE OPERATION OF THE MISSIONS.   THE CONTRACTOR SHALL IMPLEMENT A SAFETY, HEALTH, AND MISSION ASSURANCE PROGRAM THAT PROVIDES A SAFE AND HEALTHY WORK ENVIRONMENT, MINIMIZES PROGRAM RISK, AND MAXIMIZES NASA MISSION SUCCESS.  THE CONTRACTOR SHALL BE RESPONSIBLE AND ACCOUNTABLE FOR ACHIEVING THE REQUIRED RESULTS.
CORE REQUIREMENT FUNCTIONS, SUCH AS CONFIGURATION MANAGEMENT, QUALITY ASSURANCE, ETC. ARE REQUIRED TO SUPPORT IDIQ TASK ORDERS.  
THE SPACE NETWORK (SN) IS COMPRISED OF A FLEET OF ON-ORBIT TRACKING AND DATA RELAY SATELLITES (TDRS) AND ASSOCIATED GROUND SYSTEMS THAT PROVIDE TELECOMMUNICATIONS SERVICES.  THE NATURE OF THE SN ARCHITECTURE, I.E., EXTREMELY LARGE CAPITAL INVESTMENT, CONTRACTOR OPERATED FACILITIES, CONTINUOUS 24X7 REQUIREMENTS, ETC., LENDS ITSELF TO A CORE REQUIREMENTS APPROACH.  
THE GROUND NETWORK (GN) CONSISTS OF AN ORBITAL TRACKING NETWORK AND THE SATELLITE LASER RANGING NETWORK.  THE NATURE OF THE GROUND NETWORK ARCHITECTURE, I.E., DIVERSE MIX OF COMMERCIAL AND GOVERNMENT ASSETS, EVOLVING GEOGRAPHIC AND TECHNICAL CUSTOMER REQUIREMENTS, AND LEGACY SYSTEMS, ETC. LENDS ITSELF TO AN IDIQ APPROACH. 
OTHER ACTIVITIES, I.E., VERY LONG BASELINE INTERFEROMETRY NETWORK OPERATIONS AND MAINTENANCE (O&M), ELECTRONIC SYSTEM TEST LABORATORY, REQUIREMENTS DEVELOPMENT, HARDWARE AND SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT, ETC. ARE BEST SUITED TO AN IDIQ APPROACH IN THE RESOURCE-CONSTRAINED ENVIRONMENT THAT NASA OPERATES IN.

Product or Service Description: IT AND TELECOM- INTEGRATED HARDWARE/SOFTWARE/SERVICES SOLUTIONS, PREDOMINANTLY SERVICES
Description of Requirement: THE EXPLORATION AND SPACE COMMUNICATIONS PROJECTS DIVISION (ESC) IS A NATIONAL RESOURCE LOCATED AT GODDARD SPACE FLIGHT CENTER (GSFC) WHICH ENABLES SCIENTIFIC DISCOVERY AND SPACE EXPLORATION BY PROVIDING INNOVATIVE AND MISSION-EFFECTIVE SPACE COMMUNICATIONS AND NAVIGATION SOLUTIONS TO A LARGE COMMUNITY OF DIVERSE CUSTOMERS.  ESC MANAGES OPERATIONAL GEOSTATIONARY COMMUNICATIONS RELAY SATELLITES AND GROUND SYSTEMS FOR THE SPACE COMMUNICATIONS AND NAVIGATION (SCAN) PROGRAM AT NASA HEADQUARTERS. NAICS Description: OTHER ELECTRONIC AND PRECISION EQUIPMENT REPAIR AND MAINTENANCE
Product or Service Description: IT AND TELECOM- OTHER IT AND TELECOMMUNICATIONS
Description of Requirement:
NASA/GSFC HAS A REQUIREMENT TO ACQUIRE SUPPORT SERVICES FOR THE ADMINISTRATION, OPERATIONS, AND MAINTENANCE OF THE TRANSPORTABLE LASER RANGING SYSTEM (TLRS-3) LOCATED AT THE UNIVERSIDAD NACIONAL DE SAN AGUSTIN (UNSA) IN AREQUIPA, PERU, WHICH IS PART OF THE NASA SATELLITE LASER RANGING NETWORK.

THE CONTRACTOR SHALL PROVIDE THE PERSONNEL, MATERIALS, AND FACILITIES NECESSARY TO OPERATE AND MAINTAIN THE SATELLITE TRACKING STATION AT CHARACATO, AREQUIPA, PERU:

I. IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE NEW INTERNATIONAL AGREEMENT BETWEEN NASA AND THE UNIVERSIDAD NACIONAL DE SAN AGUSTIN (UNSA), WHICH WAS RENEWED BY NASA ON JUNE 10, 2014 AND ED BY UNSA ON JULY 2, 2014 (VALID UNTIL OCTOBER 25, 2019), UNSA, FOR ITS PART, SHALL FULFILL THE FOLLOWING RESPONSIBILITIES:

1. PROVIDE THE 1,450-SQUARE-METER FENCED SITE LOCATED AT THE SAN FRANCISCO OBSERVATORY IN CHARACATO, IN ADDITION TO THE BUILDINGS, EQUIPMENT AND MATERIALS OWNED BY UNSA, FOR STATION OPERATIONS.  IT IS NOTED THAT UNSA SHALL USE THE AREA SURROUNDING THE STATION AS IT SEES FIT AS LONG AS THIS USAGE IS NOT DETRIMENTAL TO THE FUNCTIONING OF THE STATION.

2. SELECT AND TRAIN, AS MUTUALLY AGREED UPON, AND IN CONFORMITY WITH NASA'S TECHNICAL PERFORMANCE REQUIREMENTS, UNSA TECHNICAL PERSONNEL RESPONSIBLE FOR THE OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE OF THE SATELLITE TRACKING SYSTEM.  UNSA SHALL ALSO BE RESPONSIBLE FOR THE ADMINISTRATIVE MANAGEMENT AND NECESSARY JANITORIAL SERVICES.  UNSA SHALL ESTABLISH PROCEDURES FOR PAYING UNSA PERSONNEL THEIR SALARIES AND SOCIAL BENEFITS.

Product or Service Description: IT AND TELECOM- ANNUAL SOFTWARE MAINTENANCE SERVICE PLANS
Description of Requirement:
SUPPORT OF IV&V OFFICE, SOFTWARE ASSURANCE TOOLS (SWAT) GROUP.
NASA IV&V SOFTWARE ASSURANCE TOOLS (SWAT) GROUP SUPPORT
THE INDEPENDENT VERIFICATION&VALIDATION (IV&V) PROGRAM IS RESPONSIBLE FOR PERFORMING INDEPENDENT VERIFICATION AND VALIDATION ON NASA MISSION-CRITICAL SOFTWARE. THE IV&V OFFICE
(IVVO), WITHIN THE IV&V PROGRAM, CONSISTS OF FOUR FUNCTIONAL GROUPS: IV&V PROJECTS (IVVP), TECHNICAL QUALITY&EXCELLENCE (TQ&E), RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT (R&D) AND THE SOFTWARE
ASSURANCE TOOLS (SWAT) GROUP. THE NASA IV&V SWAT GROUP SUPPORTS THE IV&V PROGRAM BY SERVING AS THE CENTRAL HUB FOR THE MANAGEMENT OF COMPUTER AIDED SOFTWARE ENGINEERING (CASE) TOOLS, AND OTHER TOOL-BASED ENGINEERING SERVICES. THE SWAT GROUP HAS BEEN CREATED TO PROMOTE THE SHARED USE OF ALL DEVELOPED AND COMMERCIAL CASE TOOLS HAVING APPLICABILITY TO IV&V ACTIVITIES. THE SWAT GROUP REQUIRES CONTRACTOR SUPPORT TO EVOLVE, EVALUATE, INTEGRATE, IMPROVE, AND MAINTAIN CASE TOOL SOLUTIONS BASED UPON THE NEEDS OF IV&V PROGRAM ACTIVITIES.
CONTRACTOR SUPPORT IS ALSO REQUIRED TO MAINTAIN RESIDENT EXPERT KNOWLEDGE AND PROVIDE TRAINING ON ALL DEVELOPED OR PURCHASED CASE TOOLS UTILIZED BY THE IV&V PROGRAM ACTIVITIES. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS REQUIREMENT IS TO SUPPORT THE NASA IV&V SWAT GROUP BY PROVIDING MANAGEMENT, CONTINUOUS IMPROVEMENT, TRAINING, AND ENGINEERING SERVICES OF THE IV&V COMPUTER AIDED SOFTWARE ENGINEERING (CASE) TOOLS THAT ARE UTILIZED BY THE IV&V PROGRAM.
THE RESPONSIBILITIES OF THE CONTRACTOR ARE FURTHER DESCRIBED IN SECTION 2.0 OF THIS DOCUMENT.
TO SUMMARIZE, THE CONTRACTOR SHALL SUPPORT THE SWAT GROUP IN THE FOLLOWING AREAS:
- INTEGRATING RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT (R&D) SOLUTIONS INTO THE IVVO OPERATIONAL ENVIRONMENT
- PROVIDING CONTINUOUS IMPROVEMENT OF THE SERVICES OFFERED AND THE CASE TOOLS PROVIDED AS AN OPERATIONAL CAPABILITY
- SERVING AS THE PRIMARY INTERFACE FOR CASE TOOL AND HARDWARE REQUESTS FROM IVVO GROUPS
- WORKING WITH THE IV&V PROGRAM SUPPORT OFFICE (PSO), INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (IT)
GROUP TO PERFORM ACCEPTANCE TESTING ON ALL CASE TOOLS BEING INTEGRATED INTO THE NASA NETWORK PRIOR TO PROMOTING CASE TOOLS AS AN OPERATIONAL CAPABILITY
Ultimate Parent Legal Business Name: TMC TECHNOLOGIES OF WEST VIRGINIA CORP.

Product or Service Description: IT AND TELECOM- TELECOMMUNICATIONS NETWORK MANAGEMENT
Description of Requirement: THE VENDOR SHALL PROVIDE SUPPLEMENTAL IT SUPPORT TO STMD.  THESE IT SERVICES INCLUDE THE MANAGEMENT, ANALYSIS, DEVELOPMENT, IMPLEMENTATION AND MAINTENANCE OF INTERNET-BASED WEB SITES AND APPLICATIONS THAT ARE UNIQUE TO STMD OR SPONSORED BY STMD AND SHARED WITH OTHER NASA HEADQUARTERS OR ENTERPRISE ACTIVITIES.  WITHIN THE LIMITATIONS OF THE PRICING PROPOSAL, THE VENDOR SHALL DESIGN, DEVELOP, DEMONSTRATE, EVALUATE AND DEPLOY SOLUTIONS THAT EXPLOIT EMERGING TECHNOLOGIES TO MEET STMD INFORMATION SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS.  THE VENDOR SHALL PROVIDE AN ANALYSIS OF DIFFERENT HOSTING OPTIONS AND IDENTIFY ANY MODIFICATIONS WITH THE CURRENT SUPPORT MODEL IF OPTIONS ARE OUTSIDE OF NASA HQ...THE VENDOR SHALL PROVIDE TECHNICAL WRITING SERVICES. THE VENDOR SHALL DEVELOP EDITORIAL CONTENT FOR THE STMD WEB SITE AND PROGRAM COMMUNICATION MATERIALS AS APPROVED BY THE GOVERNMENT TASK ORDER MANAGER. THESE SERVICES INCLUDE JOURNALISTIC STYLE CREATIVE WRITING AND EDITORIAL TRANSLATION OF TECHNICAL CONTENT.

Product or Service Description: IT AND TELECOM- TELECOMMUNICATIONS NETWORK MANAGEMENT
Description of Requirement: EVALUATE EMERGING TECHNOLOGIES TO RECOMMEND ENHANCEMENTS TO THE AERONAUTICS RESEARCH MISSION DIRECTORATE BUSINESS AND FINANCIAL MANAGEMENT APPLICATIONS.  PARTICULAR EMPHASIS SHALL BE PLACED ON MULTI-MEDIA SOLUTIONS, COLLABORATIVE TOOLS, KNOWLEDGE MANAGEMENT, REPORTING REQUIREMENTS AND COMMUNICATION.  TRAINING AND ATTENDANCE AT NEW TECHNOLOGY DEMONSTRATIONS AND TRADE SHOWS IS ENCOURAGED, TO IDENTIFY AND CONDUCT RESEARCH INTO EMERGING TECHNOLOGIES...DEVELOP, MAINTAIN, AND DOCUMENT THE ARMD IT ARCHITECTURE AS IT RELATES TO THE AGENCY IT ARCHITECTURE AND TO ANY LOCATIONS HOSTING ARMD SERVERS/APPLICATIONS.  CONSULT WITH ARMD, THE NASA CHIEF INFORMATION OFFICER, AND DESIGNATED TECHNICAL CONSULTANT(S) TO DEVELOP RECOMMENDATIONS FOR IMPROVEMENTS TO THE ARCHITECTURE, INCLUDING COST AND IMPACT AS PRIMARY ELEMENTS OF PROPOSED SOLUTIONS. TRAVEL TO CENTERS AND PARTNER LOCATIONS AS REQUIRED TO SUPPORT THESE ACTIVITIES. ALL TRAVEL WILL REQUIRE ARMD APPROVAL...PROVIDE TECHNICAL SUPPORT TO ARMD IN ADDING TO, CHANGING EXISTING, OR PUBLISHING WEB-RELATED MATERIAL AND IN EDITING AND FORMATTING THIS MATERIAL FOR VARIOUS MEDIA CONSISTENT WITH PRESENT AND FUTURE MISSION DIRECTORATE, AGENCY, AND FEDERAL POLICY (INCLUDING SECTION 508 OF THE REHABILITATION ACT OF 1972, ET. AL.)..DEVELOP AND EXPLOIT THE LATEST MULTIMEDIA AND INFORMATION SERVICES AND PRODUCTS FOR ARMD IN ALL FORMATS INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO PROCURE NECESSARY HARDWARE AND SOFTWARE TO SUPPORT THIS EFFORT. PROVIDE RESEARCH, DEVELOPMENT, SUSTAINING ENGINEERING, AND MAINTENANCE
